*******************************************************************************
* Walk Visualisation                                                        
*******************************************************************************

	A C++ application based on Qt, Qwt and CGAL to visualise and gather 
	statistics about Delaunay triangulations.

*******************************************************************************
* About
*******************************************************************************

	Written by:             Ross Hemsley
	E-mail:                 ross.hemsley (at) inria.fr
	Blog of current work:   http://rosshemsley.co.uk

*******************************************************************************
* Installing
*******************************************************************************

	***************************************************************************
	* Requirements
	***************************************************************************

    Requires QT4, CGAL 3.9, cmake and Qwt. 

	***************************************************************************
	* Mac users	
	***************************************************************************

	The following commands will build the app to run locally.
	    
	    $ cmake .
	    $ make 	

	To create a .dmg installer allowing drag-and-drop
	installing of the application on any mac.
		
		$ sudo make install
		$ sudo cpack -G DragNDrop CPackConfig.cmake
	
	***************************************************************************
	* Linux users	
	***************************************************************************

	The following is untested but should work.
		
		$ cmake .
		$ make
		
	***************************************************************************
	* Windows users	
	***************************************************************************
		
	Try the following link.
		
		http://www.ubuntu.com/download/desktop	
		

